      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POINT BREAK (8) struggled in tougher grade last start after settling off pace at The Meadows, but prior to that won by 2 lengths at Warragul (25.67) beating Full Noise in a Grade 4/5 on May 12. Has won three of four starts from this draw. Can discover winning form. ZIPPING SIGRID (5) has an excellent record here having never missed the placings in four starts, including two wins and two placings. Placed last time (28.87) at Sale in a Grade 4/5, finishing second and beaten 2.5 lengths. Looks suited here and can measure up. OFF THE BEER (2) produced a moderate performance last time when sixth at The Meadows over 525m behind Mystifying Lomar (30.70) in a Grade 5. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. GAS AND DUST (6) has strong credentials over this journey.",
